<exercise checkit-seed="0004" checkit-slug="SQ1" checkit-title="Sequence formulas">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                Find the first 5 terms of the following sequence:
                <ul>
                    <li><m>a_n=n^{2} + 1.</m></li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                Find a closed form for the following sequence:
                <ul>
                    <li><m>5, 20, 80, 320, 1280,\ldots</m></li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                Find a recursive form for the following sequence:
                <ul>
                    <li><m>-5, -1, 3, 7, 11,\ldots</m></li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            
            
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <ul>
                    <li><m>2, 5, 10, 17, 26</m> if you start with <m> n=1</m>, or <m>1, 2, 5, 10, 17</m> if you start with <m> n=0</m>.</li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            
            <li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Answers can vary depending on your choice of starting index.  For example, <m>5 \cdot 4^{n}</m> if <m> n=0,1,...</m>.</li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            
            <li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Answers can vary depending on your choice of starting index.  For example, if <m>a_0=-5</m> then <m>a_n=1a_{n-1}+4</m>.</li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            
           
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
